<p id="p-26">Immune response had a significant effect on number of sleep bouts (Complete 4-way ANOVA genotype:ru <i>F</i><sub>2,23976</sub> = 69.9, <i>p</i> &lt; 0.00001, GS1.32 &gt; PGRP-Lca vs. GS1.32/+: <i>F</i><sub>1,16632</sub> = 013.08, <i>p</i> = 0.0003, GS1.32 &gt; PGRP-Lca vs. +/PGRP-Lca: <i>F</i><sub>1,15840</sub> = 71.52, <i>p</i> &lt; 0.00001). See <a class="xref xref-fig" href="#fig-6" data-jats-ref-type="fig" data-jats-rid="fig-6">Figs. 6</a> and <a class="xref xref-fig" href="#fig-7" data-jats-ref-type="fig" data-jats-rid="fig-7">7</a>. <a class="xref xref-table" href="#table-3" data-jats-ref-type="table" data-jats-rid="table-3">Table 3</a> gives the means and standard errors for number of sleep bouts. This result is difficult to interpret as RU486+ GS1.32 &gt; PGRP-Lca flies have more disturbed sleep than RU486+ GS1.32/+ flies but less disturbed sleep than RU486+ +/PGRP-Lca flies.</p>
